 air and no roo=\r\nf. Though we\n spent only 5 min and left&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;  in a hurry, I was ve=\r\nry pleased with that temple. Someone from Tamil Nadu probably knows the nam=\r\ne of the temple and goddess.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; Like =\r\nthis, I am sure there are many temples with a powerful divine presence acro=\r\nss India.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; Apart from the Kaali tem=\r\nple at Dakshineshwar, one of my best experiences when meditating was at the=\r\n Krishna/Vitthal temple at Aalandi near Pune. I am sure that Jnaneshwar Mah=\r\naraj is still meditating in the underground chamber there.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; =\r\n=C3=82&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; *=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp=\r\n;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp; *=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=\r\n=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; =C3=82&nbs=\r\np;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; Even the middle of a busy road in India is better for medi=\r\ntating than a temple in USA. These western countries are so filled with raj=\r\nas and tamas. There is rajas in India too, but there is a good amount of sa=\r\nttwa there. Thus, any temple in India will be a good place to meditate, but=\r\n my view is that there is not much left at *some* temples. But some temples=\r\n are really good.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; If one has a cha=\r\nnce to spend a few months doing spiritual sadhana near a temple, I suggest =\r\nthe following:&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; Mayapur, Dakshinesh=\r\nwar, Puri and Kamakhya in east India, Kurtaalam, Tiruvannamalai (Arunachala=\r\nm hills)=C3=82&nbsp;and Narayana=C3=82&nbsp;vanam (near Tirupati)=C3=82&nbs=\r\np;in south India, Shirdi, Aalandi, Dwaraka=C3=82&nbsp;and Girnar mountains =\r\n(Junagadh) in west India, Varanasi, Vrindavan and Hrishikesh in north India=\r\n and Srisailam and Mantralayam=C3=82&nbsp;and Ujja